Aug 20 2008	First time in San Fran	This was going to be my first time in San Fran and my wife's second. Our friend recommended getting a hotel/motel off of Lombard as there were good, &quot;cheap&quot; motels in that part of the city and it's a nice part of the city. I almost went with a hotel near Union Square- glad I didn't as other than the extravagant shopping, there wasn't much else there. LMI had a good clean rooms, surprisingly comfortable beds, and excellent service. They even let us keep our luggage there after checking out so that we could have one last romp around the city without having to drag our luggage everywhere. It may have been a small action on their part but it meant a world of convenience to us. It's a great location- just a couple of blocks from buslines that will take you to any part of the city, a nice walk to the Crookedest Street area and not too far of a walk to Fillmore/Union where there were decent shops and restaurants. The staff were helpful in showing where to go and how to get there, definitely utilize the Muni as it was the easiest/cheapest way to get where you wanted to go. Of course the only complaint was the street noise, but you're in a big city so it's expected. With some good earplugs you're set. Also, after a couple of nights, we didn't really notice the noise as all of the hustle and bustle during the day put us in a deep sleep at night. Between the price, location, service and room quality, it made us feel as though we got a great deal for being in San Fran.	
