Jul 27 2007 	Great location great value no terrible surprises	We booked our room well in advance by calling the property directly. We chose this inn for its free parking and proximity to the Golden Gate Bridge because we had a wedding to attend in Marin County but still wanted to stay in SF for most of our trip. We were not disappointed. The front desk clerk was exceedingly well-mannered and helpful when we checked in. We requested and received a room in the back because I had read on TripAdvisor that it could be noisy on the Lombard Street side. Our room was clean and a good size. There was ample storage space in the closet and dresser. The sink/mirror were outside of the bathroom. The shower was the only thing I really didn't like -- the water pressure was weak and the shower head was about a foot shorter than me! I literally had to do a back-bend to get the shampoo out of my hair. It's a good thing I do yoga. The housekeepers were really nice and kept the room fresh every day during our 5-night stay. We were able to park our car every time we came into the garages. It's a little hard to maneuver in the garages, though, and almost impossible to safely emerge onto the side street from the lower-level garage. (People in SF are not polite drivers, so be careful.) We found the location to be great for taking the city buses and walking to local restaurants and shops. If we returned to SF in the near future, we would definitely consider staying here again.	
